        content: "Asma Taamallah (f) is a working student in her final year of engineering studies and an artificial intelligence intern at FIWARE Foundation. She holds an applied license in Sciences and Technologies of Information and Communication with a speciality in Networks and Telecommunication Systems from the Higher Institute of Technological Studies in Communication of Tunis. She is pursuing her engineering studies in the ICT field at the Higher School of Communication of Tunis (Sup’Com), where she was accepted in an exchange program at Offenburg University of Applied Sciences in Germany, as a scholarship holder and a member of the Baden-Württemberg Stipendium students community. Now she is close to obtaining her Telecommunication Engineering diploma from Sup’Com. During her six years of University, she has had the opportunity to work on many projects mainly in the IoT and computer vision field. Her interests are more focused on artificial intelligence and machine learning. Furthermore, she is proficient in Arabic, French, and English and she is developing new communication skills in German and Japanese. She is an Open and highly motivated individual with a strong desire to learn.", linkedin: "https://www.linkedin.com/in/asma-taamallah/", twitter: "", domain: "", location: "",
